e rambling.<br><br>Just a poor paladin traveling through Norrath. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulocrovik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Locrovik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 8:32:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> IMO paladins should get crits vs undead. Just like rangers with bows, rogues with throwing, SK's have a pet, granted it isnt that good of a pet but its extra damage.  I feel that warriors are the only class that should have natural crits vs anything.  like they already do. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40070>Locrovik's Magelo Profile</a><BR><BR><BR><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=157457">Locrovik's Guild Magic Profile</A> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaragirlancot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aragir Lancot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 706<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/02 9:33:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> Well, we've got Instrument of Nife now, and that's a HUGE boon for the lower leveled paladin.  Much more power vs undead at level 30 - 40 and we'd be overpowered.  In my opinion, of course.<br> <p><div align="center"><font size="2">Aragir Lancot<BR><BR><font size="1">"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR>Cerivel tells you, 'Hehe grats on scaring off a level 56 giant that hits for 360'<BR><BR>Paladin of the 49th shield<BR><a href="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/">Exiles</a>, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/26/02 3:33:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> I  like the idea of Paladin innate crits/crips vs undead, though it would make Combat Fury only good for getting Slay Undead.<br><br>How about this:<br><br>Give Paladins innate crits/crips vs undead only at level 15 (to go with a spell level... I dont know why, but it just appeals to me, and the crits should come a little later than Warriors get theirs.). Should be same frequency as warriors.<br>Reduce damage to 210 or perhaps 180 on Instument of Nife procs.<br><br>This is what would make the most sense to me, if something like this were ever implemented. It would not really overpower Paladins either, since the damage increase would be small (but should be significant)<br><br><br>And Aragir... I almost got to experience your sig the other day. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Got to tank a Protector of Zek after the Warrior, level 54, went down in the first 2 rounds. (of course, I died after it had gone down to less than 50%, having taken 7229 damage with only 1 CHeal that hit for 1k... Eep! Did I just say that part out loud? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) Very fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>Paladin of the 48th season<br>Tanker of the Worshippers of Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirtaino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirTainO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 2:10:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/images/pally.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> I tested Holyforge dozens of times in KC lately (only place I really can use it) and I never made more then 8 but usually not more then 3 Crits/crips against undead.<br>Usual damage per hit is around 150 with a 30/36 lance, highest ever is a 435 hit.<br><br>I am very disappointed about it.<br><br>Sure is no help at all, but just a feature which gives us the chance to maybe, once ina while, with much luck, and just very very rarely get off a nice hit.<br><br>Instrument of Nife makes like 10 times the damage Holyforge does, in the same time.<br>To me this disc us completely useless but to make a screenshot once in a while when I hit for 300+. <p><center>  <A href="http://www.jollyjokers.com/eq"><img src="http://www.jollyjokers.com/taino.jpg" border=0 alt="Legend of the Jokers Website"></a><br><b>~ <FONT color=#ffffff face=Verdana size=1><a href="mailto:taino@jollyjokers.com">Taino the Earth Caller<a href="http://www.jollyjokers.com/eq"></a></font><font size=1> ~ ICQ40865262 ~ </FONT></STRONG></FONT></FONT><FONT color=#ffffff face=Verdana size=1><STRONG><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4906">My profile</a> ~<br><br></b><EM><b><font size=2>"Strength is a matter of mind" <br></b></FONT></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 8:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> personally,  i think that slay undead as it is now is proper.  It gives higher esteem to those of us who have worked hard enough to attain the ability,  and separate himself from the crowd.<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 1:51:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> Well, I think you are absolutely right.  <br><br>My thoughts on why this didn't happen?  Basically because paladins and all the other hybrid characters were after-thoughts to Verant.  They were put in to puff up the roster of available classes which is why hybids have few unique or defining skills.  In the beginning it probably looked like an easy way for Vi to churn out content with a small development cost.  <br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 2:38:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> I don't think hybrids were an afterthought.  Paladins and the other hybrids have been in Dungeons &amp; Dragons and other games that EQ was based on for years, and hybrids were there when EQ was launched.<br><br>I think Paladins were pretty well balanced vs. warriors when EQ was launched (prior to any expansions).  The maximum level was 50, warriors didn't have ridiculous melee advantages over Paladins, and to this day I think hybrids are pretty well balanced up to level 50.<br><br>Then they released Kunark, raised the level cap to 60, and all hell broke loose.  They did an awful job keeping the classes balanced and the &quot;specialist&quot; classes like warrior, cleric, etc. ended up being a lot stronger than hybrids.<br><br>Verant has put a lot of work since then into correcting that, and at this point, at least for Paladins, I'd say they've done a pretty decent job of it.  That's one of the reasons you see people cringing at the thought of raising the level cap again with Planes of Power--people can't help but think &quot;uh oh, here we go again...&quot;.<br><br>Aalek<br>60 Crusader<br>Reign in Power <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A> at: 3/29/02 11:53:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usjoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sjoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 5:53:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> Personally I would be for addining inate crits versus undead since they caved and gave wizzards inate nuke crits. I would like to see this implemented at 11 like wizards.<br><br>Then to improve the disc holy forge would just multiply your inate crit landing chance by 3. That should then stack with combat furry such that pallies will get more crits versus undead.<br><br>Just my thoughts. <p><center><image src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jayrj1/Fironasig.jpg><Br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133603>My Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 11:43:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1> I already think that /disc holyforge should be change to a 20-30 second crit every hit(vs.undead) type disc, as it stands I use it to humour myself only. Changing it could give us the ability to finish off an undead mob quickly in a bad situation. Right now I will not use the disc unless I know I will be quickly fight 2 to 3 undead mobs in a row, lest I not get a crit at all. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>Crusader for Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utasar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tasar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 11:21:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holy mission??</span><hr size=1>   was fighting undead in madiens eye last night ,  was bored so decied to pop the ole holyforge disc .<br><br> I got 2 crits one for 582 another for 496 and i got 3 crippling blows one for 644, another for 784 and  a third for 912 damage all on the same one mob .<br><br>  was surpised as never had a crit over 500 before and never a crip over 760 before hehe.<br><br><br>  Tasarian Pureheart<br>  Crusader of Marr<br>  Sphere of Transcendence <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=80.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=80.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=10><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=80.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ez